Key Match Events: Jean-Philippe Krasso scored a third goal in these qualifiers (adding to his brace against Zambia last Friday)
Oumar Diakite doubled Ivory Coast's lead with a goal in the 55th minute
Post-Match Reflections: Les Sao’s resilience abandoned them three minutes into injury time before the interval when they allowed Jean-Philippe Krasso to score
The Elephants ensured that the visitors enjoyed a 1-0 advantage heading to the change rooms
Ivory Coast doubled their lead via Oumar Diakite to effectively end the game as a contest
Miscellaneous Highlights: Ivory Coast made it two wins from as many 2025 Africa Cup of Nations (Afcon) qualifying matches
Chad: Allabatna, Abderamane, Allarabaye (Youssouf 72’), Damba, Marius, Ngouyamsa, Ninga (Amine 73’), Osee (Abdelrazak 58’), Tchouplaou, Thiam, Yeo (Djibrine 72’)
I Coast: Y. Fofana, Adingra (Diomande 75’), Agbadou, Diakite (Traore 61’), Guessand (Diallo 61’), Kessie (Doue 75’), Krasso (Kossounou 89’), Ndicka, Operi, Seri, Singo
